00:26:34.039 --> 00:26:36.200
For the first time, I'm not repressing my feelings.

00:26:36.599 --> 00:26:37.419
I'm free.

00:26:37.579 --> 00:26:38.240
No, you're not.

00:26:39.399 --> 00:26:40.279
You should talk.

00:26:40.700 --> 00:26:42.779
You had me in the pool, and you didn't take your chance.

00:26:43.419 --> 00:26:45.779
I see the way you look at me. Why don't you just tell me how you feel?

00:26:46.039 --> 00:26:48.539
Lana, you're sick. I need to get you to a hospital.

00:26:48.659 --> 00:26:50.460
Don't avoid the question, Clark.

00:26:51.559 --> 00:26:52.879
Are you in love with me?

00:26:55.419 --> 00:26:55.740
Lana.

00:26:56.599 --> 00:26:57.460
I'm such a coward.

00:26:57.460 --> 00:26:59.000
You can't even answer a simple question.

00:27:00.059 --> 00:27:01.519
You want me? Come and get me.

00:27:03.059 --> 00:27:04.059
Lana, stop.

00:27:04.879 --> 00:27:07.299
What's the matter, Clark? Afraid of heights?

00:27:10.319 --> 00:27:12.079
What are you doing? Come down.

00:27:18.319 --> 00:27:18.839
Lana.

00:27:29.839 --> 00:27:30.339
Lana!

00:27:34.879 --> 00:27:35.720
Clark?

00:27:46.279 --> 00:27:47.700
Coming through!

00:27:48.639 --> 00:27:50.019
Grads, make it up safe.

00:27:50.859 --> 00:27:51.899
What happened?

00:27:53.099 --> 00:27:55.240
I know she's got the same symptoms as Dad and Bieles.

00:27:57.559 --> 00:27:58.700
How's Dad?

00:27:59.059 --> 00:28:01.059
He slipped into a coma.

00:28:01.059 --> 00:28:04.059
The doctors don't know how long he'll last.

00:28:14.059 --> 00:28:17.059
Mrs. Kent, I've got doctors flying in from Metropolis.

00:28:17.059 --> 00:28:19.059
I'm gonna do everything I can for Mr. Kent.

00:28:29.059 --> 00:28:36.059
Clark, I'm sorry.

00:28:36.059 --> 00:28:39.059
It's not your fault, Lex.

00:28:57.059 --> 00:28:58.059
Dr. Hamilton had a call.

00:28:58.059 --> 00:28:59.059
He said he was in a coma.

00:28:59.059 --> 00:29:00.059
He's got a copy of this book in his barn.

00:29:00.059 --> 00:29:01.059
The Nicodemus Diary.

00:29:01.059 --> 00:29:04.059
It's a firsthand account of Smallville's first mystery.

00:29:04.059 --> 00:29:06.059
In 1871, the whole settlement went postal

00:29:06.059 --> 00:29:08.059
before they even had a post office.

00:29:08.059 --> 00:29:09.059
Nice to know Smallville was still whack

00:29:09.059 --> 00:29:10.059
before the media's got here.

00:29:10.059 --> 00:29:12.059
Yeah.

00:29:12.059 --> 00:29:14.059
In the diary, they talk about a flower.

00:29:14.059 --> 00:29:16.059
The settlers called it Nicodemus.

00:29:16.059 --> 00:29:18.059
They said it liberated repressed feelings,

00:29:18.059 --> 00:29:21.059
sent them into rages, then fever, and finally...

00:29:23.059 --> 00:29:24.059
Well...

00:29:27.059 --> 00:29:28.059
All right, well, where can we find this flower?

00:29:28.059 --> 00:29:30.059
Well, let's see, that's the glitch.

00:29:30.059 --> 00:29:33.059
After the massacre, the cavalry torched the whole settlement.

00:29:33.059 --> 00:29:36.059
They wanted to make sure that whatever caused it wasn't gonna spread.

00:29:36.059 --> 00:29:38.059
The flower's been extinct for over 100 years.

00:29:38.059 --> 00:29:39.059
Well, what does Hamilton have to do with this?

00:29:39.059 --> 00:29:40.059
Isn't he a geologist?

00:29:40.059 --> 00:29:41.059
It was a meteor fixation.

00:29:41.059 --> 00:29:44.059
The tract on this paper he wrote six years ago.

00:29:44.059 --> 00:29:46.059
Metropolis University Press.

00:29:46.059 --> 00:29:48.059
I think this is the last straw.

00:29:48.059 --> 00:29:51.059
In it, he postulates that meteor rocks can be used

00:29:51.059 --> 00:29:53.059
to irradiate dormant plant cells.

00:29:53.059 --> 00:29:55.059
So you think Hamilton pulled a Jurassic Park

00:29:55.059 --> 00:29:56.059
and brought back the Nicodemus?

00:29:56.059 --> 00:29:57.059
And now he's trying to cover it up.

00:29:57.059 --> 00:29:59.059
Let's go talk to him.

00:29:59.059 --> 00:30:00.059
Wait, there's more.

00:30:00.059 --> 00:30:03.059
Dr. Hamilton didn't check out the Nicodemus diary.

00:30:03.059 --> 00:30:05.059
Lex did.

00:30:05.059 --> 00:30:06.059
You think he's involved?

00:30:06.059 --> 00:30:08.059
I told you all along he was bad news.

00:30:08.059 --> 00:30:10.059
Pete, we don't know anything yet.

00:30:15.059 --> 00:30:16.059
Good.

00:30:20.059 --> 00:30:21.059
I'll call back.

00:30:21.059 --> 00:30:22.059
I just got off the phone with the doctors.

00:30:22.059 --> 00:30:24.059
They think they've isolated the problem.

00:30:25.059 --> 00:30:26.059
Does it have to do with the Nicodemus flower?

00:30:27.059 --> 00:30:31.059
I know that you checked the diary out of the library.

00:30:31.059 --> 00:30:33.059
Yes, I did, Clark.

00:30:33.059 --> 00:30:34.059
Why?

00:30:34.059 --> 00:30:37.059
Because my property was built on the site of the original settlement.

00:30:37.059 --> 00:30:40.059
I always thought it was an interesting story.

00:30:40.059 --> 00:30:41.059
When I heard about your dad's symptoms,

00:30:41.059 --> 00:30:43.059
I remembered it, tracked it down to see if it could be any help.

00:30:43.059 --> 00:30:45.059
Why didn't you tell me about it?

00:30:45.059 --> 00:30:49.059
Clark, it's a crackpot story I was grasping at straws.

00:30:49.059 --> 00:30:51.059
Do you know Dr. Steven Hamilton?

00:30:51.059 --> 00:30:52.059
Who's that?

00:30:52.059 --> 00:30:53.059
Don't lie to me.

00:30:53.059 --> 00:30:55.059
Clark, calm down.

00:30:55.059 --> 00:30:56.059
I'm not.

00:30:57.059 --> 00:30:59.059
I know you're worried about your father and Lana,

00:30:59.059 --> 00:31:00.059
but I checked the book out of the library.

00:31:00.059 --> 00:31:01.059
That's it.

00:31:04.059 --> 00:31:06.059
I'm not responsible for what happened,

00:31:06.059 --> 00:31:08.059
and I'm doing everything in my power to fix it.

00:31:09.059 --> 00:31:10.059
That's the truth, Clark.

00:31:17.059 --> 00:31:19.059
Okay, keep your flashlight low.

00:31:20.059 --> 00:31:22.059
You're an expert on breaking and entering now.

00:31:28.059 --> 00:31:36.059
Old other.

00:31:36.059 --> 00:31:50.179
few with a

00:31:50.179 --> 00:31:54.440
pip fabulous peace

00:31:54.440 --> 00:31:56.059
again and the

00:31:56.059 --> 00:32:03.299
Pete?

00:32:07.919 --> 00:32:08.899
You looking for me?

00:32:09.539 --> 00:32:10.200
Oh, no.

00:32:11.279 --> 00:32:13.240
Do you have any idea how beautiful you are?

00:32:13.500 --> 00:32:14.799
Okay, Pete, you've been infected.

00:32:14.879 --> 00:32:15.940
We've got to get you to the hospital.

00:32:19.139 --> 00:32:19.819
That's right.

00:32:21.079 --> 00:32:21.799
Ignore Pete.

00:32:22.240 --> 00:32:23.480
He's just a funny guy.

00:32:23.480 --> 00:32:25.860
You don't have to sweat his feelings

00:32:25.860 --> 00:32:27.180
because you've only got eyes for Clark.

00:32:27.539 --> 00:32:29.380
Calm down, Pete. I'm going to call Clark.

00:32:33.180 --> 00:32:35.920
He's probably hanging out with his new best friend, Lex Luthor.

00:32:48.880 --> 00:32:49.900
Give me your keys.

00:32:50.740 --> 00:32:51.700
Why? Where are you going?

00:32:53.480 --> 00:32:57.880
I'm serious, Chloe.

00:33:00.319 --> 00:33:01.720
Give me your damn keys!

00:33:01.720 --> 00:33:02.440
Daaamn!

00:33:04.819 --> 00:33:09.579
Tamper Kim mission.

00:33:17.039 --> 00:33:17.579
Please take a cake.

00:33:17.579 --> 00:33:18.680
Thanks, David.

00:33:18.680 --> 00:33:18.759
Can't wait to get a Olsen.

00:33:19.339 --> 00:33:19.440
Jacob.

00:33:19.500 --> 00:33:20.299
I will meet you at theOncle Sam's.

00:33:20.299 --> 00:33:22.339
I really will!

00:33:23.120 --> 00:33:23.200
Hmm?

00:33:23.200 --> 00:33:23.400
...

00:33:23.480 --> 00:33:25.480
How is he?

00:33:25.480 --> 00:33:28.480
Not good.

00:33:28.480 --> 00:33:32.480
Clark, Mr. Beals died half an hour ago.

00:33:42.480 --> 00:33:45.480
With all my abilities, there's nothing I can do.

00:33:48.480 --> 00:33:51.480
What do we do if Dad...

00:33:53.480 --> 00:33:56.480
...doesn't want to see me?

00:33:57.480 --> 00:34:01.480
Did I ever tell you about the first time I ever saw him?

00:34:04.480 --> 00:34:06.480
No.

00:34:07.480 --> 00:34:10.480
He came to Metropolis U to take a finance course.

00:34:10.480 --> 00:34:15.480
And he was sitting by a fountain, all denim and flannel, eating an apple.

00:34:15.480 --> 00:34:18.480
And I asked to borrow his notes.

00:34:18.480 --> 00:34:21.480
He didn't know that I was the note-taker for the class.

00:34:21.480 --> 00:34:23.480
He still does.

00:34:23.480 --> 00:34:25.480
You're sly, Mom.

00:34:28.480 --> 00:34:31.480
He was so cute.

00:34:32.480 --> 00:34:39.480
So I asked him for his notes, and he just handed over his notebook without even asking my name.

00:34:39.480 --> 00:34:42.480
And I said, how can you be so sure I'll bring it back?

00:34:42.480 --> 00:34:46.480
And he said, I prefer to believe in people.

00:34:49.480 --> 00:34:51.480
It sounds like Dad.

00:34:51.480 --> 00:34:53.480
And I remember looking at him.

00:34:53.480 --> 00:34:56.480
I was completely embarrassed because I was thinking the dumbest thing.

00:34:56.480 --> 00:35:01.480
I was thinking, God, I hope he marries me.

00:35:01.480 --> 00:35:08.480
I still think that every day there's a part of me that says, God, I hope he marries me.

00:35:19.480 --> 00:35:21.480
I'm sorry, Mrs. Kent.

00:35:21.480 --> 00:35:24.480
Can I talk to you for a second, clerk?

00:35:24.480 --> 00:35:26.480
Go.

00:35:37.480 --> 00:35:39.480
I'm so sorry.

00:35:39.480 --> 00:35:40.480
Dr. Hamilton was lying.

00:35:40.480 --> 00:35:42.480
I found the Nicodemus flower in the barn.

00:35:42.480 --> 00:35:44.480
One got Pete, and he took a really quick turn to scary.

00:35:44.480 --> 00:35:45.480
Where did he go?

00:35:45.480 --> 00:35:48.480
He grabbed a gun, and he said he was going after Lex.

00:35:51.480 --> 00:35:59.019
This flower has existed for hundreds of years.

00:35:59.900 --> 00:36:03.400
Now, the Native Americans must have developed some sort of herbal antidote,

00:36:03.559 --> 00:36:05.320
and these are the instructions.

00:36:05.579 --> 00:36:06.240
Where'd you find it?

00:36:06.340 --> 00:36:07.900
Collecting dust in some old museum.

00:36:08.059 --> 00:36:09.940
Now, it's a one-of-a-kind, so they're gonna want it back.

00:36:09.980 --> 00:36:11.920
I'll get it up to my team in Metropolis immediately.

00:36:12.320 --> 00:36:13.179
Nobody's going anywhere.

00:36:15.960 --> 00:36:16.400
Pete.

00:36:18.519 --> 00:36:19.539
What are you doing here?

00:36:21.480 --> 00:36:23.280
I knew you were behind this.

00:36:23.599 --> 00:36:25.460
You pretended to be Clark's friend, but you're not.

00:36:27.800 --> 00:36:29.480
And now his dad's gonna die.

00:36:31.019 --> 00:36:31.880
Because of you.

00:36:32.340 --> 00:36:33.039
What's this about?

00:36:33.199 --> 00:36:34.340
Do not pretend you don't know!

00:36:34.740 --> 00:36:35.679
I went to your barn!

00:36:36.139 --> 00:36:36.860
He's infected.

00:36:38.599 --> 00:36:41.579
Pete, we have the cure. We're gonna make everyone better.

00:36:41.980 --> 00:36:42.920
You're nothing but a liar.

00:36:43.579 --> 00:36:44.820
Clark can't see it, but I can.

00:36:45.079 --> 00:36:45.940
And now you're gonna pay.

00:36:46.079 --> 00:36:46.320
No.

00:36:51.480 --> 00:36:57.820
Pete, if that book is destroyed, you and Lana and Mr. Ken will all die.

00:36:58.240 --> 00:36:58.860
You're lying.

00:36:59.760 --> 00:37:00.840
Pete, I want to help you.

00:37:00.860 --> 00:37:02.380
You don't want to help anybody but yourself!

00:37:04.079 --> 00:37:06.539
You come to town, and suddenly you're Clark's new best friend!

00:37:08.840 --> 00:37:10.599
I used to think he was a good judge of character.

00:37:11.380 --> 00:37:12.179
Lex, the book.

00:37:15.099 --> 00:37:16.900
Pete, I'm gonna reach in there and grab that book.

00:37:18.719 --> 00:37:19.800
If you want to shoot me.

00:37:21.480 --> 00:37:22.980
Go ahead.

00:37:24.159 --> 00:37:25.039
No problem.

00:37:28.840 --> 00:37:31.320
Get out!

00:37:38.920 --> 00:37:40.320
Say goodbye, Lex.

00:37:40.980 --> 00:37:41.539
Pete!

00:37:42.240 --> 00:37:43.280
Don't do it!

00:37:43.840 --> 00:37:44.980
We used to be best friends.

00:37:45.960 --> 00:37:47.360
His dad screwed over my dad,

00:37:47.980 --> 00:37:49.659
and now he's trying to screw up things between us.

00:37:50.000 --> 00:37:51.460
The world's a better place without us.

00:37:51.480 --> 00:37:52.480
You're not gonna get away with this.

00:37:52.480 --> 00:37:52.840
Not with me.

00:37:52.840 --> 00:37:52.940
I'm not gonna get away with this.

00:37:52.940 --> 00:37:52.980
You're not gonna get away with this.

00:37:52.980 --> 00:37:53.079
You're not gonna get away with this.

00:37:53.079 --> 00:37:53.860
Pete, put the gun down.

00:37:54.280 --> 00:37:55.480
He's behind all this.

00:37:55.559 --> 00:37:56.940
I saw Hamilton here.

00:37:58.699 --> 00:38:00.400
They're working on this together.

00:38:01.460 --> 00:38:02.260
Is that true?

00:38:02.860 --> 00:38:05.019
Clark, he's delusional.

00:38:05.740 --> 00:38:06.740
I don't believe you.

00:38:07.740 --> 00:38:08.420
You're right, Pete.

00:38:08.740 --> 00:38:09.740
He's been lying to everyone.

00:38:10.360 --> 00:38:11.559
Yeah, I know who my true friends are.

00:38:11.940 --> 00:38:12.780
I knew you'd see the light.

00:38:18.019 --> 00:38:20.059
Clark, what are you doing?

00:38:20.240 --> 00:38:21.320
You can't talk your way out of this one.

00:38:21.320 --> 00:38:22.820
I see you.

00:38:22.920 --> 00:38:23.620
You really are.

00:38:24.180 --> 00:38:25.220
Friendship is over.

00:38:30.140 --> 00:38:30.920
Nice one.

00:38:31.920 --> 00:38:32.620
I'll finish you.

00:38:36.400 --> 00:38:37.300
How'd you do that?

00:38:38.280 --> 00:38:39.160
Don't worry, Pete.

00:38:39.300 --> 00:38:40.080
We'll get you to the hospital.

00:38:48.860 --> 00:38:50.000
Clark, what the hell?

00:38:50.000 --> 00:38:50.039
No.

00:38:51.320 --> 00:38:51.980
I'm sorry, Lex.

00:38:55.640 --> 00:38:56.559
So that was an act?

00:38:57.460 --> 00:38:58.480
I didn't know what else to do.

00:38:58.519 --> 00:38:59.100
He was gonna shoot you.

00:39:01.180 --> 00:39:02.340
You had me for a moment.

00:39:02.420 --> 00:39:03.420
I thought you were serious.

00:39:04.280 --> 00:39:05.940
They feed you on that farm.

00:39:08.640 --> 00:39:09.740
Was Hamilton really here?

00:39:11.260 --> 00:39:12.340
What do you think, Clark?

00:39:12.340 --> 00:39:12.420
I don't know.

00:39:21.320 --> 00:39:26.940
You still can't talk about Gordon.

00:39:26.940 --> 00:39:27.180
You won't touch him?

00:39:27.200 --> 00:39:27.620
So what?

00:39:27.660 --> 00:39:28.400
You can't feed us?

00:39:28.519 --> 00:39:28.960
No.

00:39:29.000 --> 00:39:29.059
I can actually feed you something.

00:39:29.100 --> 00:39:29.280
Here.

00:39:30.420 --> 00:39:31.300
No.

00:39:31.380 --> 00:39:31.820
You can't eat anything.

00:39:31.860 --> 00:39:33.140
We should eat our own insects.

00:39:33.200 --> 00:39:36.539
dawg!

00:39:36.620 --> 00:39:38.960
We're not eating our own insects.

00:39:39.000 --> 00:39:40.840
Have you taken up that rat test yet?

00:39:40.920 --> 00:39:41.600
Uh-uh.

00:39:41.660 --> 00:39:42.720
Don't do nothing but thumbnail.

00:39:42.800 --> 00:39:43.780
Have fun, Lincoln.

00:39:43.800 --> 00:39:45.640
The water's boiling at 100 feet.

00:39:45.700 --> 00:39:46.940
So will terrńsk display technology.

00:39:47.000 --> 00:39:47.880
You might be okay.

00:39:47.920 --> 00:39:48.580
I'll tell you that now.

00:39:48.600 --> 00:39:49.100
How come he doesn't call me at night?

00:39:49.160 --> 00:39:49.220
Wait.

00:39:49.280 --> 00:39:49.559
What?

00:39:49.640 --> 00:39:50.300
Why does that care.

00:39:50.340 --> 00:39:50.680
Oh, wait a minute.

00:39:50.679 --> 00:39:51.839
American remedy.

00:39:51.839 --> 00:39:53.259
How are Pete and Lana?

00:39:53.259 --> 00:39:56.019
They're already up.

00:39:56.019 --> 00:39:57.940
Dad, do you remember anything?

00:39:57.940 --> 00:39:58.839
No.

00:39:58.839 --> 00:40:00.779
Doctors think it's because of the fever.

00:40:00.779 --> 00:40:02.079
Trust me, it's better that way.

00:40:02.079 --> 00:40:02.980
Come on.

00:40:02.980 --> 00:40:03.879
We're going to talk.

00:40:03.879 --> 00:40:04.779
Oh, sweet.

00:40:09.779 --> 00:40:11.679
Dr. Hamilton, hello.

00:40:20.679 --> 00:40:38.559
What'd you do with my lab?

00:40:38.559 --> 00:40:39.460
I destroyed it.

00:40:39.460 --> 00:40:40.359
How dare you?

00:40:40.359 --> 00:40:42.219
You're lucky you found a cure nobody infected

00:40:42.219 --> 00:40:44.019
can remember anything.

00:40:44.019 --> 00:40:45.440
The people are talking.

00:40:45.440 --> 00:40:46.960
I'm sure Beals worked for my father,

00:40:46.960 --> 00:40:49.159
and then there's Chloe Sullivan.

00:40:49.159 --> 00:40:50.679
I'm sensing this relationship

00:40:50.679 --> 00:40:51.579
is over.

00:40:51.579 --> 00:40:53.179
No, Doctor.

00:40:53.179 --> 00:40:54.500
I think you're very talented.

00:40:54.500 --> 00:40:57.859
You just need closer supervision.

00:40:57.859 --> 00:40:59.980
I recently acquired a small research facility

00:40:59.980 --> 00:41:03.000
outside Metropolis, Cadmus Labs.

00:41:03.000 --> 00:41:06.579
I'm going to hide you out there.

00:41:06.579 --> 00:41:10.299
Remember, Lex, you're the one opening Pandora's box.

00:41:10.299 --> 00:41:11.679
I'm just the key, Dr. Hamilton.

00:41:20.679 --> 00:41:27.079
OK.

00:41:27.079 --> 00:41:28.079
Open your eyes a little.

00:41:33.799 --> 00:41:36.460
It's Metropolis.

00:41:36.460 --> 00:41:37.359
It's beautiful.

00:41:40.359 --> 00:41:42.919
I can't believe we're up here.

00:41:42.919 --> 00:41:44.179
It's actually getting down, which

00:41:44.179 --> 00:41:45.379
is going to be the interesting part.

00:41:45.379 --> 00:41:46.279
Ahem.

00:41:46.279 --> 00:41:49.179
Yeah.

00:41:49.179 --> 00:41:50.539
It's good to have you back, love.

00:41:50.539 --> 00:41:56.599
I spent the entire day apologizing to the talent

00:41:56.599 --> 00:41:59.960
staff, and to Lex, and to Whitney.

00:41:59.960 --> 00:42:03.380
